1 SECTION 2. A new subsection to section 23.1-07-06 of the North Dakota Century Code is
2 created and enacted as follows:
3 Administer the wastewater infrastructure grant program.
4 SECTION 3. APPROPRIATION - DEPARTMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL QUALITY -
5 WASTEWATER INFRASTRUCTURE GRANTS - STRATEGIC INVESTMENT AND
6 IMPROVEMENTS FUND - ONE-TIME FUNDING. There is appropriated out of any moneys in
7 the strategic investment and improvements fund in the state treasury, not otherwise
8 appropriated, the sum of $25,000,000, or so much of the sum as may be necessary, to the
9 department of environmental quality for the purpose of providing wastewater infrastructure
10 grants, for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027. No more than
11 $12,500,000 may be awarded for a project. Of the funding appropriated in this section, at least
12 $12,500,000 must be awarded to cities with a population less than twelve thousand five
13 hundred, based on the most recent federal decennial census. If less than $12,500,000 has
14 been awarded to cities with a population less than twelve thousand five hundred by April 1,
15 2027, the department may award the remaining funds to other eligible projects. The funding
16 provided in this section is considered a one-time funding item.
